vectorData.altText:
Neurons are both structurally and functionally polarized; i.e. the two ends are different from each other, both physically and functionally. Neurons function in information transfer, and information is conducted unidirectionally, from the input “pole” of the neuron to its output “pole”.
Dendrites: input
numerous, highly branched, tapering, short
Cell body (soma): input
genetic and metabolic centre of cell
Axon (“nerve fibre”):  integration, output
1 axon / cell, of variable length, \ neurons may fxn. locally or distantly
may have axon collaterals; end as:
Synaptic terminals: transfer of info
chemical transfer of info to the target cell via synaptic transmission
target cell type varies (nerve, muscle, gland)
